description: Using a multimeter or scope referenced to the power‑supply negative, monitor the voltage at the two input terminals of the load module over at least one full 20‑s cycle while the main lamp is observed flickering off for ~0.5 s. Check whether the 12 V at the load‑module input remains steady or briefly drops/interrupts when the lamp goes out., outcome='The load-module input voltage at the positive lead is approximately 11.83–11.84 V and remains close to nominal over the measurement interval.  \nThe negative lead of the load-module input sits near ground (about 0.03–0.05 V).  \nThe main load lamp is lit and shows no observable internal fault.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=50.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> series diode in load module (ahead of lamp and indicator),
description: While the system is operating and the main lamp is exhibiting its ~0.5 s dropout every ~20 s, probe the voltage on both sides of the series diode inside the load module with respect to the supply negative. Observe whether the voltage feeding the lamps (diode output node) briefly drops toward 0 V or otherwise changes when the lamp goes dark, even though the input to the load module remains steady., outcome='The inspection panel was opened successfully.  \nThe load protection diode shows a steady anode voltage of 11.8277 V and cathode voltage of 11.0551 V with respect to supply negative on both measurements, with no observed change during the lamp dropout.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module lamps (main lamp and internal indicator),
description: Using the inspection panel and peephole, observe both the main external lamp and the internal indicator lamp continuously over several 20‑s cycles, specifically during the ~0.5‑s dropout. Verify whether (a) both lamps extinguish together, (b) only the main external lamp goes dark while the internal indicator remains lit, or (c) the external lamp actually remains lit and only appears to dim due to some optical/visual effect., outcome='The inspection panel was opened successfully, but the peephole could not be opened because the enclosure is not openable. During observation, both the Main Load lamp and the Internal Indicator Lamp were lit with no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> visual observation of main load lamp (external to enclosure),
description: Carefully observe the main load lamp from the user’s normal viewing position for at least two full 20‑s cycles in a darkened room, without opening any panels. Note precisely whether its apparent 0.5‑s turn‑off still occurs, or whether the lamp appears continuously lit from this vantage point., outcome='The main load lamp (bulb) is lit during observation and shows no observable internal fault. The simulator notes that the circuit did not converge and is in an unstable or oscillating state.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> inter‑module cabling and polarity between power, control, and load modules,
description: Visually inspect and verify the physical connections and polarity of all plug‑together cables between the power‑supply, control (ambient sensor), and load modules. Confirm that each module’s 12 V and 0 V terminals are correctly matched (no reversed plug or swapped pair) and that no extra or missing connections are present., outcome='All inspected cables show consistent polarity: each (+) cable is connected only to other (+) cables, and each (−) cable is connected only to other (−) cables. No extra or missing plug‑together connections were found between the power‑supply, control, and load modules.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=100.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
